chapters.title: Intro
What are two primary prerequisites for salvation?
According to Jesus, how important is baptism? John 3:5
What directive did Jesus give to his disciples? Matt. 28:19-20
Most people believe that any style or type of Baptism is acceptable as long as a person is sincere; but what does the Bible say about this? Ephesians 4:5
Who was the first person to practice Bible baptism in the New Testament? [Mark 1:9]
Jesus was baptized in the river, not in Jerusalem with someone sprinkling water from a bowl on Him.
Why was John Baptist baptizing near Salim? [John 3:23]
Peter 2:211 For even hereunto were ye called: because Christ also suffered for us, leaving us an example, that ye should follow His steps
And the angel of the Lord spake unto Philip, saying, Arise, and go toward the south unto the way that goeth down from Jerusalem unto Gaza, which is desert

And he arose and went and, behold, a man of Ethiopia, an eunuch of great authority under Candace queen of the Ethiopians, who had the charge of all her treasure, and had come to Jerusalemfor to worship
How were these "other" methods of baptism incorporated in Christianity? [Matt. 13:24-25]

John Wesley was in America in 1737, he was tried by a jury of thirty-four men in a church trial on the charge of "refusing to baptize Mr. Parker's child, except by dipping." It seems clear, therefore, that John Wesley, the father of Methodism, recognized baptism as immersion. The records of this trial are found in the court proceedings of Georgia
Baptism is not the end of the Christian life. It is the beginning.
What are some of the benefits one receives after baptism?
Every sin is FORGIVEN. [Acts 2:38] 2. The HOLY SPIRIT is GIVEN to us. Mark 110, Acts. 5:32
We are ADOPTED into God's heavenly [Phillip 3:20]
What are some of the requirements for Bible baptism as outlined in the Scriptures?
Go ye therefore, and teach all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Ghost
And he took them the same hour of the night, and washed their stripes, and was baptized, he and all his, straightway
Are there biblical grounds for re- baptism?
And he said what then were ye baptized? And they said, Unto John's baptism.
